01/12/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- EU security chief Javier Solana has sent a letter to Montenegrin opposition leader Predrag Bulatovic, discussing issues related to next year's planned independence referendum, regional news agencies reported Wednesday (30 November). According to his spokesperson, Cristina Gallach, Solana said any decisions regarding the referendum must be made after the EU-backed Venice Commission presents its recommendations. (Tanjug, Beta - 30/11/05)
